HEADWORD: hoodooism
<hw>hoodooism</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Voodoo, a form of religion
practiced chiefly in Caribbean countries (esp.
<country>Haiti</country>); it involves witchcraft and animistic
deities.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> voodoo, vodoun, voodooism.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

